July 7th is Tanabata.🎋
Tanabata is a Japanese Festival celebrated on July 7th.
・
On this day, people decorate bamboo branches with paper strips.
・
It is believed that a wish comes true when you write on the paper strips and hang them on the bamboo branch.
・
Also It is said that Tanabata is a special day for lovers because it is the day where lovers reunite.
・
Have a beautiful day! 🎋
・
・

Bellissimo tramonto❤️
・
・
I started traveling alone when my first cancer treatment was over. 
I needed strength to get over cancer. 
I want to keep my heart strong and live beautifully.  How many beautiful places can I visit ... for the rest of my life.  I'd like to share the beautiful scenery with my dear friends. 
Let's all seek the happiness and enjoy a one-time life!  It’s the best way for living every day.
What a wonderful life! 
I love you guys!🌹 ・
